On December 17, 2020, several nominations and appointments were sent to the Senate. Terrence M. Andrews of California was nominated to be a Judge of the United States Court of Federal Claims for a term of fifteen years, replacing Edward J. Damich whose term had expired. Romolo A. Bernardi of New York was nominated to be a Governor of the United States Postal Service for a term expiring on December 8, 2023, replacing Carolyn L. Gallagher whose term had expired. Daniel Z. Epstein of Texas was nominated to be Chairman of the Administrative Conference of the United States for a term of five years, replacing Paul R. Verkuil who had resigned. However, the nomination of Daniel Z. Epstein to be a Judge of the United States Court of Federal Claims for a term of fifteen years, replacing Edward J. Damich, was withdrawn. This nomination had originally been sent to the Senate on February 4, 2020.